COVID Primary Screen Analysis

Amanda Mok

9/18/2020

Fig. 1: Well-performing guides tend to lie within 500nt of a gBlock boundary; this pattern is observed at 10 fM, 100 fM, and 1 pM activator concentrations.

Fig. 2: Guides with high rates above background (no activator) tend to not have structured spacers [Fig 2a], but do not tend to fall within single-stranded regions as predicted by SHAPE-MaP and/or DMS-MaPseq [Fig 2b]. However, the majority of guides have small rate increases over background; as such, these differences may be due to small sample size and are not statistically significant (p>0.4).

No observable correlation between 10fM rates and spacer GC or A content.

Similar patterns were observed with rates measured at 100fM and 1pM.
